OL,3,CMan jailed for three years for killing
OL,4,Cwife
OL,6,FHe told the operator he had hit her
OL,7,Fwith a hammer and when asked if she
OL,8,Fwas dead, Baird replied "I think so".
OL,10,FPolice and paramedics attended the
OL,11,Fcouple's home where they observed a
OL,12,Fheavily-bloodstained Baird sitting in
OL,13,Fthe kitchen with a wound to his head.
OL,15,FThey then discovered Mrs Baird who was
OL,16,Flying slumped on a sofa in a small
OL,17,Froom off the kitchen. She was
OL,18,Fpronounced dead at the scene.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G6/14
