OL,3,CMan jailed for three years for killing
OL,4,Cwife
OL,6,FShe sustained catastrophic wounds to
OL,7,Fher head whilst her husband - who was
OL,8,Fbleeding from self-inflicted injuries
OL,9,Fto his head - was agitated and
OL,10,Fconfused at the scene.
OL,12,FAlso present was the hammer Baird used
OL,13,Fin the fatal attack.
OL,15,FFollowing his arrest, Baird admitted
OL,16,Fattacking his wife with a hammer and
OL,17,Fsaid 'the voices in my head told me to
OL,18,Fdo it'.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G7/14
