OL,3,CMan jailed for three years for killing
OL,4,Cwife
OL,6,FAfter he was arrested in the aftermath
OL,7,Fof his wife's death, Baird was
OL,8,Fsectioned and spent a period of time
OL,9,Fdetained under the Mental Health Act.
OL,11,FHe was then moved to prison and
OL,12,Fsubsequently pleaded guilty to a
OL,13,Fcharge of manslaughter which was not
OL,14,Faccepted by the Crown.
OL,16,FBaird stood trial earlier this year on
OL,17,Fa charge of murdering his wife.
OL,19,FThe trial commenced in January in
OL,20,Ffront of a jury who heard five days of
OL,21,Fevidence.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}           G10/14
