OL,3,CMan jailed for three years for killing
OL,4,Cwife
OL,6,FHowever, as the murder trial was due
OL,7,Fto enter its second week, a legal
OL,8,Fissue arose which was dealt with in
OL,9,Fthe absence of the jury.
OL,11,FAfter making a ruling on the legal
OL,12,Fissue, trial judge Mr Justice
OL,13,FMcFarland determined that the jury
OL,14,Fshould be discharged.
OL,16,FThe case was listed again in May and
OL,17,Fon that occasion, Baird pleaded again
OL,18,Fguilty to a charge of the manslaughter
OL,19,Fof his wife Susan Baird by way of
OL,20,Fdiminished responsibility.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}           G11/14
